<section id="fs-id1368215" class="short-answer" type="short-answer">
<title>Short Answer</title>
<exercise id="fs-id1961548" type="short-answer">
<problem id="fs-id1317363">
<para id="import-auto-id2732010">Track the social stratification of your family tree. Did the social standing of your parents differ from the social standing of your grandparents and great-grandparents? Are there any exogamous marriages in your history? Does your family exhibit status consistencies or inconsistencies?</para>
</problem>
</exercise>
<exercise id="fs-id2647957" type="short-answer">
<problem id="fs-id2726150">
<para id="import-auto-id1302570">Review the concept of stratification. Does your family have wealth? What is the overall family income? What kind of employment do your caregivers/parents/guardians have? Where would you guess you fall within the social classes (low, middle, or high)? </para>
</problem>
</exercise>
<exercise id="fs-id1296833" type="short-answer">
<problem id="fs-id3028123">
<para id="import-auto-id3600297">Where did your family grow up? What is their understanding of the American Dream and how you can achieve it? Does your family share the same understanding of stratification?</para>
</problem>
</exercise>
